The United Nations has imposed new sanctions on North Korea in response to the country's repeated ballistic missile tests. These sanctions include a ban on exporting goods and services and cutting off foreign investors. The article praises President Trump and UN Ambassador Nikki Haley for rallying the UN Security Council into taking action. The sanctions are expected to cause significant economic pain to North Korea. China's support for the sanctions is seen as a result of the belief that Trump may take military action against North Korea. The article argues that Trump's approach has strengthened American diplomacy and sets an important precedent for dealing with other countries, such as Iran, that are advancing their ballistic missile programs.